                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Crude, irregular.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black (bleak), red</seg>
                        Scribe: Walda Giyorgis. According to
                        the colophon, the scribe is Walda Giyorgis (his baptismal name; his worldly
                        mane is däbtära Fänta) of Säqʷäṭa Gabrǝʾel, who was brought up by Wag sǝyyum
                           Bǝrru.<date>Late 19th century (?)</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the donors; name of the king;
                           a few lines of the incipit pages of Texts I-1 – I-7, alternating with
                           black lines; incipit of each commemorative notice; the word salām;
                           elements of Ethiopic numerals; elements of the punctuation signs and text
                           dividers.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#189vb">f. 189vb</locus>
                           <desc>: Register of the donors' names.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> List of the names of the donors written in red and reddish-brown
                              ink. </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Two strips of parchment originating from another Ms.
                           have been inserted between fols. 1 and 2.
 - <locus from="190ra" to="191vc">190ra-191vc</locus>: Fragment of another Synaxarion for the
                           month of Ṗagʷǝmen serving as endleaves. The text is partly illegible on
                           fols 191r-v.
 - Erasures: <locus target="#5ra">5ra</locus>,
                           104ra.
 - Corrections written over erasures: <locus target="#10va">10va</locus>, 22rc; in recent blue ballpoint pen: <locus target="#8rc">8rc</locus>.
 - Omitted letters or words inserted
                           interlineally: e.g., <locus target="#69vc">69vc</locus>, 77va, 78rc,
                           79va, 81ra.
 Scribbles and doodles: <locus target="#151v">151v</locus>, 162r, 162v, 163r.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
